      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHES ALLABOUTLUV NZ (3) saluted two runs back then recorded a comfortable victory last time out, scoring by 9 metres over 2200m at this track. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. That latest effort is good enough to take out a race like this. BETTABLACK TIGER (6) is a quality entire who has managed two wins and two minor placings from four starts this prep. Produced another fine effort last start when he finished third over 2200m at this track, beaten 6 metres. This looks a sterner test than last time but on his best form he is capable of testing his rivals. INTRUSION (4) is the next elect off a last-start win by 2.25 metres at this track over 2200m. WAVES OF CHANCE (2) saluted two runs back then his luck changed last time when he broke and finished a long way back in seventh over 2579m at Hobart. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Must get things right but if he does a big run is on the cards.",
